{"questionId":"22807","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A group of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1280</mn></math> students were asked which electronic device they preferred. The results per age group are given in the following table.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/0fd31d861a6c88bc1b537b05c812d52636a40858.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>χ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> test for independence was performed on the collected data at the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo></math> significance level. The critical value for the test is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>277</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the number of degrees of freedom.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22807","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.1c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the number of degrees of freedom.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}